@startmindmap
* eUTXO vs Bitcoin UTXO
** Shared foundation (UTXO)
*** Value as discrete coins, not balances
*** Consume whole inputs, create outputs
*** Change like physical cash
*** Inputs = outputs + fee (exact)
*** UTXO immutable, spent once
*** UTXO set = current state
** Bitcoin output
*** Value + locking script (scriptPubKey)
*** Unlock with scriptSig / witness
*** Script: stack-based, not Turing-complete
*** Sees mainly the unlocking data
*** Time locks: nLockTime, CLTV, CSV
*** No per-UTXO state, no native assets
** What "Extended" adds
*** Datum: state attached to a UTXO
*** Redeemer: argument at spend time
*** Script context: whole-transaction view
** Consequences
*** Expressive validators (Plutus / Aiken)
*** Stateful contracts (consume + recreate)
*** Native multi-asset UTXOs
*** Covenants natural (constrain outputs)
** Preserved from UTXO
*** Deterministic validation
*** Fail-fast, atomic, no partial state
*** Explicit concurrency (fan-out, batching)
@endmindmap
